@node intro "Introduction"
@next legal
@toc main

@{b}Introduction - What is HTMLdir ?@{ub}

        HTMLdir recursively list the content of a directory in HTML files.

        Main features:

        - HTML files can be created in the processed directory or in an other
        directory (useful when using HTMLdir on a CDROM for instance);

        - an index of all the subdirs processed can be created;

        - this index can be displayed in a frame;

        - files can be sorted by name, size or date;

        - types of listed files are shown thanks to icons;

        - a background and a title image can be used;

        - thumbnails mode;

        - easy deletion of created files;

        and some other surprises ! 

@endnode

